018package org.opengis.metadata.quality;

020import org.opengis.annotation.UML;
021
022import static org.opengis.annotation.Specification.*;

025/**
026 * Degree to which data are stored in accordance with the physical structure of the data set.
027 * The data set is described by the {@linkplain DataQuality#getScope() scope}.
028 *
029 * <h2>Standardized values</h2>
030 * In order to achieve well defined and comparable quality information, it is recommended to
031 * report data quality using {@linkplain Measure quality measures} listed in ISO 19157 annex.
032 * The following table provides a summary; see ISO 19157 for more complete descriptions and examples.
033 * All identifiers should be in "ISO 19157" namespace.
034 *
035 * <table class="ogc">
036 *   <caption>Standardized values derived from ISO 19157</caption>
037 *   <tr>
038 *     <th>{@linkplain MeasureReference#getMeasureIdentification() Identifier}</th>
039 *     <th>{@linkplain MeasureReference#getNamesOfMeasure() Name of measure}</th>
040 *     <th>{@linkplain Measure#getBasicMeasure() Basic measure}</th>
041 *     <th>{@linkplain Measure#getValueType() Value type}</th>
042 *     <th>Remarks</th>
043 *   </tr><tr>
044 *     <td>119</td>
045 *     <td>physical structure conflicts</td>
046 *     <td>error indicator</td>
047 *     <td>Boolean</td>
048 *     <td>{@code true} indicates physical structure conflict</td>
049 *   </tr><tr>
050 *     <td>19</td>
051 *     <td>number of physical structure conflicts</td>
052 *     <td>error count</td>
053 *     <td>Integer</td>
054 *     <td></td>
055 *   </tr><tr>
056 *     <td>20</td>
057 *     <td>physical structure conflict rate</td>
058 *     <td>correct items rate</td>
059 *     <td>Real</td>
060 *     <td></td>
061 *   </tr>
062 * </table>
063 *
064 * <p>{@linkplain Measure#getDefinition() Definitions}:</p>
065 * <ol start="119">
066 *   <li>Indication that items are stored in conflict with the physical structure of the data set.</li>
067 *   <li value="19">Count of all items in the data set that are stored in conflict with the physical structure of the data set.</li>
068 *   <li>Number of items in the data set that are stored in conflict with the physical structure of the data set
069 *       divided by the total number of items.</li>
070 * </ol>
071 *
072 * @author  Martin Desruisseaux (IRD)
073 * @author  Cory Horner (Refractions Research)
074 * @author  Alexis Gaillard (Geomatys)
075 * @version 3.1
076 * @since   2.1
077 */
078@UML(identifier="DQ_FormatConsistency", specification=ISO_19157)
079public interface FormatConsistency extends LogicalConsistency {
080}
